properties.accomplishments:
After being undercut by non-union shops during the Great Recession, this union firm negotiated an agreement with the union that they would launch a non-union spinoff, by agreeing that it would run entirely on its own non-union labor force and infrastructure.  The owners’ goals were to be the best in the market on both the union and non-union side.
Challenge was intensified by industry known for drawing independently-minded craftsman employees. 
Analyzed practices, roadblocks, and safety hazards. Initiated comprehensive training across both companies.
•	Defined guiding principal everyone could be excited about: “Quality carpentry faster.” This simple phrase helped change-averse carpenters understand why they needed to deviate from tradition and follow company processes.
•	Positioned companies—one a startup and one a regional icon—as largest of their kind with reputation for speed, quality work, and professionalism. Respectively, they became the largest employers of non-union and union framers in their market.
•	Improved relations with insurance company and union after observing hazards, initiating safety training, and writing and teaching training drills.
•	Empowered owners to schedule build-projects congruent with long-term priorities, making the tough decision to turn down work that was not specifically in the multi-family complex vertical, or that did not fit their schedule. Both companies now function from position of strength; and, both now set projects, timeframe, and price in alignment with business goals.

Company wanted to restructure its design-and-build process to differentiate quality, maximize margins, and still deliver on the promise of value to consumers. Capitalized on industry connections and expertise to explore business models. Recruited and hired team member to specialize in value engineering. Transformed service-oriented business into production model by adopting Ford’s assembly-line process.
•	Brought company from startup to $15M in annual sales with an effective and profitable business model that weathered many industry cycles. Designed, built and sold hundreds of new homes.
•	Achieved control of building costs and timeframe while providing quality, custom-feel homes. 
•	Earned multiple Registered Builder awards and recognition from fellow builders for excellence.

properties.accomplishments:
* Identified approximately $3M in cost savings in 15 categories for YRC. 

* Leveraged Coupa P2P system to integrate purchasing system with accounts payable system to provide control and visibility of transaction lifecycle. 

* Created and executed category procurement strategies to reduce costs and mitigate business risks. Demonstrated keen business acumen. 

** Analyzed internal and external data points to evaluate purchasing decisions and  benchmarked within industry to ensure YRC received competitive pricing and best in class services.  

* Conducted total cost of ownership (TCO) to identify cost savings and process improvement opportunities; achieved $1.3M in savings. 

* Executed agreement for small parcel auditing services; negotiated 25% fee reduction and $40K in guaranteed service refunds from common carrier.  

* Recouped 50% of prepaid software premiums from Coupa through strategic category and cost savings assessments.  
* Negotiated 6% rate reduction for contingent workforce program by identifying program compliance concerns. 

* Launched RFP for plastic retail bag category to address quality and compliance concerns. Solicited 54 qualified suppliers, developed requirements based on quantifiable measures, delivered 30% rate reduction and 8% annual cost savings. 

* Reduced corrugate supplies expense by $100K through aggressive contract negotiations. 

* Delivered 30% rate reduction, 8% annual cost savings  quarterly third party quality testing funded by the supplier, failure to perform penalties and monthly quality reporting for retail bags. 

* Led platform system migration, resulting in numerous process improvements reducing administrative burden by 65%, increased program efficiencies and 12% cost savings. 

* Overhauled exterior retail store sign program; rationalized supply base, negotiated 15% rate reduction and increased program compliance from zero to 80%. 
* Designed, developed, and launched 4 new products; doubled product offerings and achieved $3M+ in incremental annual revenues at significantly higher profitability in business with declining opportunity. 

* Improved sales performance of key product lines by 10% through development and implementation of product road maps, new market introductions, vertical segmentation, and sales training. 

* Improved price realization through rigorous financial analyses; generated $1.5M+ increase in profits annually. 

* Supported sales channel to achieve 102% of revenue goals for FY15 with collateral and lead generation campaigns. 
* Developed and executed 2015 peak season plan for contingent workforce, resulting in 100% coverage and high percentage of resources converted to full-time; developed go forward peak season plans. 

* Implemented enterprise-wide MSP/VMS to streamline contingent workforce program. 

* Overhauled promotional items/company store vendor framework; created tighter program controls and monitored processes to increase annual budget value to $80K; negotiated improved terms to save $2M and revised rebate structure. 

* Revised overaggressive travel savings target made by consulting firm and exceeded new $1M target; reduced number of participating hotels 50% by increasing rate compliance and enforcing program and booking-tool policy. 

* Negotiated $6M in multi-year savings to exceed FY14 cost savings goal of 21%; identified contract weaknesses and opportunities to increase margin. 

* Delivered multiple process improvements for internal customer, Global Vehicles resulting in $500K in savings. 

* Reduced vehicle wash services rogue spend $9M and realized $6M in savings by creating first centralized vehicle wash program; decreased 50 suppliers to 6 and implemented standardized reporting. 
* Secured $8M, one-time tax credit and $1M in annual charge reversals; earned Bravo Zulu Award for developing process, mechanism, and monthly monitoring procedures tracking bad debt charges and for leading cross-functional team charged with identifying and recovering bad debts. 

* Negotiated $1M waiver for late payment/filing penalties, reduced annual tax assessments 65%, and decreased preparation time up to 2 days by automating processes and developing plan to address number of late/incorrect filing assessments. 

* Secured $500K refund credits and $3M reduction in audit assessments from Michigan state audit by identifying monthly overpayments resulting from overlooked tax exemptions and negotiating with local jurisdictions.
